**Q5 (Hard, English):**  
Explain why the **z**eta function \(\zeta(s)\) has no zeros for \(\text{Re}(s) > 1\).

**Answer Key:**  
- The Euler product formula shows \(\zeta(s) = \prod_p (1 - p^{-s})^{-1}\) for \(\text{Re}(s) > 1\), implying \(\zeta(s) \neq 0\) in this region.

